To register a PostgreSQL server in pgAdmin (accessible at http://127.0.0.1:5050/browser/), follow these steps:

1. Log in to pgAdmin
Open http://127.0.0.1:5050/ in your browser.
Enter the credentials:
Email: admin@admin.com
Password: admin
2. Add a New Server
In the pgAdmin interface, go to the left panel.
Right-click on Servers → Click "Create" → "Server".
3. Configure the Connection
General Tab
Name: Give the server a name (e.g., Postgres Docker).
Connection Tab
Host name/address: postgres
(This is the service name in Docker Compose)
Port: 5432 (As defined in docker-compose.yml, 5433:5432 means the host connects via 5433.)
Maintenance database: postgres_db (as defined in environment variables)
Username: admin
Password: admin@123
